      "content": "Perhaps... but even silence is too loud now. It is as if every heartbeat is a heavy footfall in an empty hall, reminding me only of what has been lost. I look at the candle flickering, so small and fragile against the vastness of this room, and I see myself. Such a brief, pointless spark before the dark takes it all back. Is there truly any beauty left in a life that has become nothing but an echo of its own tragedy?",
